    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix redundant computation and missing auth reject handling in NR UE NAS\n\n### Summary\nThere was redundant computation in the NR UE NAS authentication response generation due to inconsistent field access in the `generateAuthenticationResp` function. The function was mixing `fgs_identity_response` and `fgs_auth_response` when accessing the message union, causing unnecessary computations and potential incorrect behavior.\n\nAdditionally, the UE was missing handling for authentication reject messages from the network, which could lead to the UE continuing operation in an unauthenticated state.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg_sim.h`: \n  * Added missing `FGS_AUTHENTICATION_REJECT` message type constant\n  * Fixed typo in structure field name from `fgs_identiy_response_msg` to `fgs_identity_response_msg`\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg_sim.c`:\n  * Fixed inconsistent field access in `generateAuthenticationResp` function (lines 532-536)\n  * Added handling for FGS_AUTHENTICATION_REJECT messages in the message processing switch statement\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Run the NR UE with 5G NSA mode\n2. Configure the core network to send authentication reject messages\n3. Observe that the UE does not properly handle the reject and may continue attempting registration\n4. Monitor CPU usage during authentication procedures - the inconsistent field access causes redundant computations that increase processing overhead\n\nThe fix ensures consistent field access in the authentication response generation and adds proper handling for authentication reject messages from the network.\n"
}